claim.claim-text:
An operation control method for a device including a storage section (53) arranged to store content data, an input section arranged to accept a transmission instruction of the content data stored in the storage section (53), and a transmitting section (52) arranged to transmit the content data on the basis of the transmission instruction accepted by the input section (51,52), the operation control method characterized by comprising:
counting (S20) a predetermined time (α) from arbitrary timing after start of operation of the storage device;
detecting (S23) a reproduction time of the content data;
carrying out control (S39) to stop the operation of the storage device if detecting that neither the input section nor the transmitting section is operating after the counting of the predetermined time; and
setting (S25) the reproduction time detected about the content data transmitted by the transmitting section as the predetermined time if the transmitting section transmits the content data.
